<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Characterized by wooly appearance and yellow to orange discs, and distinguished from similar species 
<taxonomicName class="Ascomycetes" family="Discomycetes" genus="Lachnum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lachnum novoguineense subsp. var. var. yunnanicum" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="variety" species="novoguineense" subSpecies="var." variety="yunnanicum">Lachnum novoguineense var. yunnanicum</taxonomicName>
in having shorter ascospores.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
