<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The tropical species 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. bambusina" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="bambusina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. bambusina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Ascomycetes" family="Discomycetes" genus="Lachnum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lachnum albidum subsp. var. var. americanum" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="variety" species="albidum" subSpecies="var." variety="americanum">Lachnum albidum var. americanum</taxonomicName>
(Dennis) W.Y. Zhuang also occur on bamboo sheaths. However, compared with the present fungus, the former has smaller ascospores and filiform paraphyses (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4114399" author="Dennis, RWG" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="289 - 348" refId="B15" refString="Dennis, RWG, 1954. Some inoperculate discomycetes of tropical America. Kew Bulletin 9 (2): 289 - 348, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4114399" title="Some inoperculate discomycetes of tropical America." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4114399" volume="9" year="1954">Dennis 1954</bibRefCitation>
), and the latter has extremely large asci and ascospores (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4114758" author="Dennis, RWG" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="418 - 458" refId="B16" refString="Dennis, RWG, 1960. Fungi venezuelani: III. Kew Bulletin 14 (3): 418 - 458, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4114758" title="Fungi venezuelani: III." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4114758" volume="14" year="1960">Dennis 1960</bibRefCitation>
). In cool-temperate to subarctic zones, 
<taxonomicName class="Leotiomycetes" family="Lachnaceae" genus="L." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="L. asiaticum" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="asiaticum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">L. asiaticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
